  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p>\r\n<p>Add the wedges to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 30-35 min or until the wedges are crispy and coloured</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>mayonnaise</strong> with 2&nbsp;tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>lemon juice</strong> (keep the rest for later) and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and set aside &ndash; this is your <strong>lemon mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>sugar snap</strong> <strong>peas</strong> roughly</p>\r\n<p>Heat a pot with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sugar snaps</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>water&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover and cook for 3 min or until the peas have turned bright green</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile,&nbsp;strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, chop the leaves finely and set aside</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the <strong>sugar snaps</strong> to a <strong>food&nbsp;</strong><strong>processor</strong> with a little squeeze of the remaining <strong>lemon</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz into a mushy paste&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Return the <strong>mushy&nbsp;sugar snap peas</strong>&nbsp;to the cooking pot and set aside&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>capers</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, carefully add the <strong>capers</strong> and cook for 1-2 min until they have puffed up a little, then transfer them to kitchen paper with a slotted spoon and set aside until serving &ndash; these are your <strong>crispy capers</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Only</strong> <strong>proceed to this step once your wedges are cooked...</strong></p>\r\n<p>Return the pan, with the remaining <strong>oil</strong> to a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Pat the <strong>cod</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>dry and season with a little <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;the pan is hot, add the <strong>cod</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 2 min, flipping halfway through (your fish is cooked once it flakes easily)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>mushy</strong> <strong>sugar snap</strong> <strong>peas</strong> to a medium heat for 1 min to warm through</p>\r\n<p>Once warmed, remove from the heat and stir in the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mint </strong>&ndash;&nbsp;these are your <strong><strong>minted mushy sugar snaps</strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/643.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cod</strong>&nbsp;with the <strong>wedges&nbsp;</strong>and <strong>minted mushy</strong> <strong>sugar snaps</strong> to the side&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle over the <strong>lemon mayo</strong> and scatter with <strong>crispy capers</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the remaining <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges for a garnish and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
